Came here on a lunch date. Outdoor seating with social distancing was in place which is always a plus for me. There were quite a few seating options, so we were seated quickly. Our waitress offered us hand sanitizer, which I liked, and gave us menus. Everything looked apitizing, that we took longer than usual to make up our minds.  I came to the conclusion with the shrimp shumai and the Volcano Roll which consisted of spicy crunch scallop & avocado inside, topped with sweet shrimp & yuzu tobiko. My date had the Miso soup, and the Pink Lady Roll which consisted of salmon tempura, yellowtail, tuna avocado & masago roll in a pink...yes pink soy paper!! we decided on wine and settled on plum wine.  As the food came out, it was a beautiful sight to see. The plating for the rolls was amazing! Being place on a Japanese traditional rectangular plate with the rolls on top of a bamboo leaf. I didn't want to touch my meal as it was just to eye pleasing. As I took my chopsticks and tasted one of my rolls I knew it was not long before my plate would be empty. The flavors of all the ingredients meshed together yet tasting each one. The yuzu tobiko (flying fish roe) definitely added an extra flair to the taste.  The pink lady was said to have an interesting taste although might not be eye catching with the pink paper wrapping. The Miso soup however, was said to be pleasingly tasteful with all natural ingredients. As far as our wine it was delicious, being sweet and strong. We would've given five stars, but there were quite a few bees that seemed to be buzzing around quite often,but I would still stop by this establishment again.
Amazing, manicured, impeccable and genuine!!

They've also had different ice cream flavors each visit to finish off the meal.  Definitely worth checking out.

I was also pleasantly surprised that the wasabi was real wasabi, not the usual paste you'd see in lower price sushi places.  Totally recommended! I don't think you'd go wrong getting sushi here.

Celebrated my best friend's graduation here! It's peaceful, charming, and the sushi is pretty & delicious! Although it is pricey, the quality matches. And honestly, I wanted everything on the menu! The seafood tasted really fresh as well!  TNT Lover ($18)-5/5 Presentation was seriously on point for this dish. It's freaking beautiful and also delicious at the same time! This was probably my favorite dish!  Lobster Tuna Roll ($18)-3.5/5 This dish was also decent, but the green sauce in the center didn't really go that well together. I think it just went better with the soy sauce.  Seared Tuna ($14)- 4/5 The tuna was yummy with a little dip of soy sauce and kinda thinly sliced. It wasn't stringy or fishy, which was nice!  Scallop ($5)-4/5 The scallop seriously melts in your mouth, although there really isn't a strong flavor, the texture makes you in awe of how soft and delicate these scallops are!
